entities.name: British bulldog
entities.description: An iconic British breed that has seen a doubling in ownership. However, the breed is prone to several health issues including ear infections, skin infections, and obesity.

entities.name: Ear infections
entities.description: A common health issue in British bulldogs, with 12.7% of the breed suffering from it.

entities.name: Brachycephalic Obstructive Airway Syndrome (BOAS)
entities.description: A health issue in British bulldogs that is often overlooked by owners, with only 3.5% of the breed being diagnosed with it.
